															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1267048&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183493" alt="Ihp" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1267048)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;" >Ihp</a></span> <span class="odate time_1403842007 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Jun 2014 04:06</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2059300">
									

<p>Right, this is what a Maxwellist Holy Writ looks like. And before you ask, as far as I can tell, this is all valid Javascript, but for some reason, I was never able to get it to compile properly in any compiler I could find. If somebody can tell me the reason why, this would be greatly appreciated.</p>
<p>This is kind of cheating, as this covers two 'objects', or rather, two anomalies: the Pineal Gland from <a href="/implanting-god">Implanting God</a> and the Signal that was received alongside it. Hedwig (yes, I am serious about that name) never needed one because she was so close to her God, WAN.</p>
<p>Anyway. I hope you enjoy reading this more than I enjoyed writing it. spending about three-odd hours sticking code in compilers only to have it return error message after error message until I just said &quot;f*ck it&quot; was not exactly fun.</p>

							</div>

								
					
